radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 1 cm with mild surrounding fat stranding and inflammatory changes. At the origin of the appendix, the lumen is obliterated and there is avid enhancement. No intra-abdominal, retroperitoneal or pelvic lymphadenopathy. The lung bases, cardiac chambers, liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, and visualized small bowel appear unremarkable.
